{"id": "ChIJG7yDPOG5woARbOdgWDOzLNo", "rating": 4.5, "userRatingCount": 286, "displayName": {"text": "hello82 LA", "languageCode": "en"}, "reviews": [{"name": "places/ChIJG7yDPOG5woARbOdgWDOzLNo/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tWVVRFbHBXR3g2WTE5dVdreEljVFZPWTNaTVNuYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "7 months ago", "rating": 1, "text": {"text": "HORRIBLE EXPERIENCE!!! i’ve been to the hello82 in san diego before and had amazing experiences with the staff. this time, i decided to go the LA location for the Plave pop up that started just today. I was deeply disappointed with the experience from the Los Angeles branch…. Not only did they horrifically underestimate sales, the “pop up” area was half heartedly made and almost sad to look at… The albums sold out within minutes of opening, which was disappointing as many people traveled to experience one of Plave’s first official events in the USA. You would expect there to be sufficient stock but unfortunately, that’s not the case.\n\nBesides that, the event space gave me flashbacks to the infamous Willy Wonka experience a while back that blew up online… It definitely seemed like there was a lack of care for the event. The “pop up” included a measly 6x6 inch box display to take photos with and a “life size” version that was basically falling apart with how poorly made it was.\n\nI’ve definitely seen better spaces and execution at the San Diego location so to see this in Los Angeles was disappointing. I don’t know if it’s the lack of care towards Plave or if your company was looking down on the group and its fan base, but this event looked like a group of kindergarteners made the props. Not only was this a poorly planned and hardly-executed event, it’s an opportunity for revenue that was indubitably missed.\n\nI fear I won’t be making the trip to LA for any pop ups in the near future until the company learns to respect the artists they work with and puts in a little more effort for their fan base as well.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "HORRIBLE EXPERIENCE!!! i’ve been to the hello82 in san diego before and had amazing experiences with the staff. this time, i decided to go the LA location for the Plave pop up that started just today. I was deeply disappointed with the experience from the Los Angeles branch…. Not only did they horrifically underestimate sales, the “pop up” area was half heartedly made and almost sad to look at… The albums sold out within minutes of opening, which was disappointing as many people traveled to experience one of Plave’s first official events in the USA. You would expect there to be sufficient stock but unfortunately, that’s not the case.\n\nBesides that, the event space gave me flashbacks to the infamous Willy Wonka experience a while back that blew up online… It definitely seemed like there was a lack of care for the event. The “pop up” included a measly 6x6 inch box display to take photos with and a “life size” version that was basically falling apart with how poorly made it was.\n\nI’ve definitely seen better spaces and execution at the San Diego location so to see this in Los Angeles was disappointing. I don’t know if it’s the lack of care towards Plave or if your company was looking down on the group and its fan base, but this event looked like a group of kindergarteners made the props. Not only was this a poorly planned and hardly-executed event, it’s an opportunity for revenue that was indubitably missed.\n\nI fear I won’t be making the trip to LA for any pop ups in the near future until the company learns to respect the artists they work with and puts in a little more effort for their fan base as well.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "kait", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116671342025242546739/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzdhTTFiQfMHsauQe7bmO06LAgnD4rqb5_fsfhxzo-Ty4-rTO_tA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo"}, "publishTime": "2025-12-03T23:01:20.081596286Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tWVVRFbHBXR3g2WTE5dVdreEljVFZPWTNaTVNuYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tWVVRFbHBXR3g2WTE5dVdreEljVFZPWTNaTVNuYxAB!2m1!1s0x80c2b9e13c83bc1b:0xda2cb3335860e76c"}, {"name": "places/ChIJG7yDPOG5woARbOdgWDOzLNo/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21KVVZqSndWVEZKYW05bWJYZFVhR00xUmw5VU5GRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "10 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "We were in town for a Kpop concert and stopped in the following day. It is a cute place with fun experiences and socializing. My daughter found some great items.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "We were in town for a Kpop concert and stopped in the following day. It is a cute place with fun experiences and socializing. My daughter found some great items.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Izzy", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100145361018850803891/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVLLP6h9c1FEK65LEvhjX61PyN6xb-SiEx9buNVmdZsPMjpan4Ifg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3"}, "publishTime": "2025-08-19T04:18:22.547021971Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21KVVZqSndWVEZKYW05bWJYZFVhR00xUmw5VU5GRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21KVVZqSndWVEZKYW05bWJYZFVhR00xUmw5VU5GRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2b9e13c83bc1b:0xda2cb3335860e76c"}, {"name": "places/ChIJG7yDPOG5woARbOdgWDOzLNo/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pGSVNHdDNZVWRJVkVWdFNuQkZNbk56U0V0cVUxRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "10 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Went to the Monsta X pop-up and it was so fun!! They really put on a great event and the merch for sale is awesome! Great deals!!", "languageCode": "en"}, "ori